social_posts.post_text:
Great show at @thevenicewest last night featuring two amazing artists, @garrisonstarr and @glenphillipsmusic! First off, The Venice West is a great new venue. As a lover of the music scene in #losangeles, it’s great to have a spot like it on the west side. 

This was my first time seeing Garrison and she was amazing. Ability to Instantly and authentically connect with her audience and her voice is beautifully unique. Got to meet her post her set and she couldn’t have been nicer and genuinely grateful to meet with her new fans. She crushed a @snoopdogg #ginnjuice cover!

Obviously a long time (since the beginning) fan of Glen’s and he played some his new music intermixed with some of his and @toadthewetsprocket’s classics. He clearly is still at the top of his game offering something for everyone from sing alongs to soulful looks into his life.

They were a power duo up there on stage representing singer songwriters in the best way possible.

Thanks for an awesome night!

Today has been hard. 

We said goodbye to our dog Baxter who was a part of the family for 17 years. He was kid  #1, Ethan and Mira’s first words (dogeeee), always first to hang his head out of the car window and my first @instagram pic in 2011.

He was the perfect dog, always available to cuddle, play catch or dress up for Halloween with the kids. 

We are grateful to have had him for 17 years of unconditional love.

RIP Baxter Edwards. We will miss you terribly.

#happymothersday to @elise.edwards.180. As our kids celebrate their 13th and 14th years and our marriage it’s 18th in September, I can’t imagine being on this wild and crazy ride with anyone else. Wishing you the bestest Mother’s Day ever!

Another @yposmb #PresidentsRetreat is in the books!  This year we headed to @chilenobayauberge in #cabosanlucas in #mexico. 

I am so happy that we are back to full strength in @ypoglobal as there is something special that happens when we get together in person that is impossible to replicate virtually. 

We heard the story of how @c.j.macias conquered his @100footwave and surfed with him as well. He also led us in a #laughingyoga class which was unexpectedly awesome.

We heard how @louislombardi navigated his unconventional journey to stardom with grit, creativity…and cooking. 

We listened to @redbullmotorsports driver @amikkelsenrally share his stories from the world of #rallycar #racing.

But most importantly we learned from eachother, made new friends and cemented our relationships with each other. We also received a momento of our #spiritanimal.

Thanks to @arashisocal @did_s0me0ne_say @hurstandsons @erikhuberman @joshmagicwand and everyone else who made the retreat a truly stellar few days!

#surfing #retreat #retreats #ypo #yposmb #yposantamonicabay

Exciting day today in the Edwards house.  I got to take Mira to get her first #guitar at the legendary  @mccabesguitarshop.  With the goal of being the next @taylorswift, the first song we are learning together is The 1. While I got her the new axe, a @taylorguitars academy series, I may steal it for some sets as it’s a beaut!

Looking forward to some more great #daddydaughter #bonding time and having her forge her own musical path.

Thank you @thekennyloggins for a great final show here in #losangeles @youtubetheater. 

He is simply a #legend.  With an awesome catalog of music that has become the #soundtrack to growing up, #love, #parenthood…and #caddyshack, @topgunmovie and #footloose of course, his music has always been incredibly relatable, inspirational and has provided an #anthem within reach at all times.  #thisisittour 

Great opening band in @yachtrockrevue!  Set the tone for an overall nostalgically awesome evening!

Finally getting around to posting my @u2 videos from when I was in Vegas for #hlth2023 and saw them at the @spherevegas.  If this is the future of concerts, the future is in good hands. 

It was hard not to be totally immersed in the experience and if you are going to be in #lasvegas, this is simply a can’t miss event. 

Bono and the band did an incredible job and their songs have been a soundtrack to my life.  My 1st concert where I slept out for tickets was the Joshua Tree Tour in ‘88.

This was the concert right after the invasion of Israel and I was incredibly humbled by how the band handled the situation dedicating Pride - In the Name of Love to those who were victims in Israel the day before. It was an emotional moment bringing people together in a time of division. May the hostages be returned safely and we find peace during these difficult times. 

#u2 #concert #spherevegas #thesphere
